    88	
    89	<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->
    90	## 4. REQUIREMENTS
    55	<!-- ANCHOR:purpose -->
    56	## 2. ROOT PURPOSE
    57	
    58	Per opencode official docs (`https://opencode.ai/docs/skills`, `/agents`, `/commands`), opencode's project-level discovery looks for **`.opencode/skills/`**, **`.opencode/agents/`**, **`.opencode/commands/`** (all plural). This repo uses singular for all three, so opencode's built-in discovery silently fails on every dispatch. This packet aligns the repo with opencode convention.
    59	
    60	Surfaced today during packet 095 (sk-code-review playbook execution): every `opencode run` printed `"Could not find any skills directories. Tried: <project>/.opencode/skills"` before falling through to the `opencode-skills` plugin's bridging behavior. Plural alignment removes that workaround dependency.
    61	
    62	The migration decomposes into four phases — one per category — to keep each phase independent and verifiable.
    63	<!-- /ANCHOR:purpose -->
    64	
    65	<!-- ANCHOR:children -->
    66	## 3. SUB-PHASE CONTROL
    67	
    68	| Order | Sub-phase | Purpose | Status |
    69	|---|---|---|---|
    70	| 1 | `001-skills` | Rename `.opencode/skills/` → `.opencode/skills/`; update 7,464 reference-bearing files; patch opencode.json + .claude/settings.local.json + skill_advisor.py | Pending |
    71	| 2 | `002-agents` | Rename `.opencode/agents/` → `.opencode/agents/`; update 1,532 files; patch CLAUDE.md §5 + sk-prompt graph-metadata + runtime_capabilities.json + audit_descriptions.py (agent half) | Pending |
    72	| 3 | `003-commands` | Rename `.opencode/commands/` → `.opencode/commands/`; update 1,811 files; patch audit_descriptions.py (command half) + target_manifest.jsonc + mcp-doctor.sh | Pending |
    73	| 4 | `004-symlinks` | Redirect 5 symlinks in `.claude/`, `.codex/`, `.gemini/` to point at the new plural targets | Pending |
    74	<!-- /ANCHOR:children -->
    75	
    76	<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->
    77	## 4. SCOPE BOUNDARY
    78	
    79	### In scope
    80	- `git mv` of three directories at `.opencode/` level (skill→skills, agent→agents, command→commands).
   380	**Sycophancy Warning:** If you notice yourself wanting to agree with the code author's intent or inflate findings to seem thorough — that is the bias this protocol exists to catch. Trust the evidence, not your inclination.
   381	
   382	---
   383	
   384	## 11. ANTI-PATTERNS
   385	
   386	**Never approve without security scan**
   387	- Security issues are P0 by default
   388	- Auth/input/output code MUST be scanned
   389	- "Looks safe" is not acceptable
   390	
   391	**Never use vague feedback**
   392	- BAD: "This could be improved"
   393	- GOOD: "Line 45: Use `safeParseInt()` instead of `parseInt()` to handle NaN case (Correctness)"
   394	
   395	**Never score without rubric reference**
   396	- Every score must cite rubric dimension
   397	- Scores must be reproducible
   398	- No "I feel like it's a 75"
   399	
   400	**Never block without P0 evidence**
   401	- FAIL/BLOCK requires documented P0 issues
   402	- Cannot block on style preferences alone
   403	- P1 issues are required fixes to pass, but are not immediate blockers
   404	- Suggestions (P2) do not justify rejection
   405	
   406	**Never ignore project context**
   407	- Project patterns override general best practices
   408	- Check existing code for established conventions
   409	- Ask for pattern documentation if unclear
   410	
   411	**Never review your own output**
   412	- Reviewers cannot review code they helped write
   413	- Self-review defeats the purpose
   414	- Request different agent for review if conflict
   415	
   416	**Never let sycophancy bias findings**
   417	- Do not inflate severity to appear thorough (phantom issues)
   418	- Do not approve readily to avoid conflict (missed issues)
   419	- Run adversarial self-check (§10) on all P0/P1 before finalizing
   420	- Evidence from code must override gut feeling in both directions

